Kubernetes  Workloads
=====================
Stateless web application
Stateful web application

Workload deals with lifecycle management of pods.


Typres of kubernetes workload
=============================

Pods
=====
apiVersion: v1
kind: Pod
metadata:
 name: web-app
spec:
 containers:
 - name: web-server
   image: nginx:latest  # Replace with the image of your web application
   ports:
   - containerPort: 80  # Expose port 80 within the container

Deployment Controller
======================
Deployment controller manage the creation,deletion,scaling of pods.



Deployment
Replicasets
pods

Deployment manages replicaset to ensure desired number of pods are running.


apiVersion: apps/v1
kind: Deployment
metadata:
 name: web-app
spec:
 replicas: 3  # Number of replicas (instances) of the application to run
 selector:
   matchLabels:
     app: web-app
 template:
   metadata:
     labels:
       app: web-app
   spec:
     containers:
     - name: web-server
       image: nginx:latest  # Replace with the image of your web application
       ports:
       - containerPort: 80  # Expose port 80 within the container



apiVersion: batch/v1
kind: Job
metadata:
 name: web-app-job
spec:
 template:
   metadata:
     name: web-app-pod
   spec:
     containers:
     - name: web-server
       image: nginx:latest  # Replace with the image of your web application
       ports:
       - containerPort: 80  # Expose port 80 within the container
     restartPolicy: Never  # Job pods are not restarted upon failure
